theorem Topology.iterate_closure_interior_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (n : ℕ) :
    ((fun S : Set X => closure (interior S))^[n]) A ⊆ closure A := by
  induction n with
  | zero =>
      -- For `n = 0`, the `0`-th iterate is the identity function.
      simpa using (subset_closure : A ⊆ closure A)
  | succ n ih =>
      -- Abbreviate the `n`-th iterate applied to `A`.
      set T := ((fun S : Set X => closure (interior S))^[n]) A with hT
      -- An arbitrary point `x` in the `(n.succ)`-th iterate.
      intro x hx
      -- Step 1:  `x ∈ closure (interior T)` by unfolding the iterate.
      have hx₁ : x ∈ closure (interior T) := by
        simpa [Function.iterate_succ_apply', hT] using hx
      -- Step 2:  `closure (interior T) ⊆ closure T`
      have h₁ : closure (interior T) ⊆ closure T :=
        Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure (X := X) (A := T)
      -- Hence `x ∈ closure T`.
      have hx₂ : x ∈ closure T := h₁ hx₁
      -- Step 3:  From the induction hypothesis `T ⊆ closure A`,
      --           get `closure T ⊆ closure A`.
      have h₂ : closure T ⊆ closure A :=
        closure_mono (ih.trans subset_rfl)
      -- Conclude that `x ∈ closure A`.
      exact h₂ hx₂

theorem Topology.isClosed_iff_closure_subset_self {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    IsClosed A ↔ closure A ⊆ A := by
  constructor
  · intro hA_closed
    -- For a closed set we have `closure A = A`, so the desired inclusion follows.
    have h_eq : closure A = A := hA_closed.closure_eq
    simpa [h_eq] using (subset_rfl : closure A ⊆ closure A)
  · intro h_subset
    -- If `closure A ⊆ A`, then equality holds, hence `A` is closed.
    have h_eq : closure A = A := by
      apply subset_antisymm h_subset
      exact subset_closure
    simpa [h_eq] using (isClosed_closure : IsClosed (closure A))

theorem Topology.closure_interior_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    closure (interior (∅ : Set X)) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  simpa [interior_empty, closure_empty]
